## üí° WHAT THIS MEANS

### ‚úÖ YES, You Can:
- Build a racing team website ‚Üí **FREE**
- Use for your business ‚Üí **FREE**
- Customize for a client and charge them for YOUR work ‚Üí **FREE**
- Use on unlimited different projects ‚Üí **FREE**
- Modify every line of code ‚Üí **FREE**

### ‚ùå NO, You Can't:
- Sell the template on ThemeForest ‚Üí **NOT ALLOWED**
- Charge someone just for the template files ‚Üí **NOT ALLOWED**
- Rebrand and sell as "Your Template" ‚Üí **NOT ALLOWED**
- Include in a paid course as "exclusive content" ‚Üí **NOT ALLOWED**

### üí≠ Gray Area Examples:

**Q: Can I charge a client $500 to build them a website using this template?**
A: YES! You're charging for your services (customization, deployment, etc.), not the template itself.

**Q: Can I include this in my web design agency's toolkit?**
A: YES! As long as you're not selling the template separately.

**Q: Can I use this for a SaaS product?**
A: YES! Free to use for any type of project.

**Q: Can I remove the credit comment from the code?**
A: NO. Keep the copyright notice in the code.

**Q: Can I fork this on GitHub and improve it?**
A: YES! Please do! Just maintain the license and attribution.

